From 13d7563197ffe613ddd73c49f40b3743e3584c65 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Steffen <steffen.roemer@orkitec.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 15:45:05 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] Vulkan: call base RenderSystem::shutdown()

Every other render system (GL3Plus, D3D11, Metal, ...) starts its
shutdown() by calling the base RenderSystem::shutdown(), which destroys
the depth buffers and all render targets - including the windows.

VulkanRenderSystem::shutdown() never did (the window-destruction block
was #if 0'd out), so VulkanWindow and its resources outlived the
VulkanDevice: the window's VMA-backed depth texture was still allocated
when ~VulkanDevice ran vmaDestroyAllocator(), tripping the VMA debug
assertion

    "Some allocations were not freed before destruction of this memory
     block!" (vk_mem_alloc.h, IsEmpty() in VmaDeviceMemoryBlock::Destroy)

and aborting debug builds on exit. The window was then torn down by the
base ~RenderSystem long after its device was deleted.

Calling the base shutdown() first (right after the device stall)
destroys the windows while the device and allocator are still alive,
matching the other render systems. The base method also handles the
depth buffer cleanup, so the local _cleanupDepthBuffers() call and the
dead #if 0 block are dropped.

Tested on macOS 15 / MoltenVK 1.4.1 (debug build): clean exit, no VMA
assertion, no change in rendering behaviour.
---
 .../Vulkan/src/OgreVulkanRenderSystem.cpp     | 27 ++++---------------
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 22 deletions(-)

diff --git a/RenderSystems/Vulkan/src/OgreVulkanRenderSystem.cpp b/RenderSystems/Vulkan/src/OgreVulkanRenderSystem.cpp
index ecb1b1a..b4ce3d8 100644
--- a/RenderSystems/Vulkan/src/OgreVulkanRenderSystem.cpp
+++ b/RenderSystems/Vulkan/src/OgreVulkanRenderSystem.cpp
@@ -271,29 +271,12 @@ namespace Ogre
             return;
 
         mDevice->stall();
-#if 0
-        {
-            // Remove all windows.
-            // (destroy primary window last since others may depend on it)
-            RenderWindow *primary = 0;
-            WindowSet::const_iterator itor = mWindows.begin();
-            WindowSet::const_iterator endt = mWindows.end();
-
-            while( itor != endt )
-            {
-                if( !primary && ( *itor )->isPrimary() )
-                    primary = *itor;
-                else
-                    OGRE_DELETE *itor;
 
-                ++itor;
-            }
-
-            OGRE_DELETE primary;
-            mWindows.clear();
-        }
-#endif
-        _cleanupDepthBuffers();
+        // destroys the depth buffers and render targets (incl. windows) like
+        // the other render systems do - their Vulkan resources (e.g. the
+        // VMA-backed window depth texture) must be released while the device
+        // and its allocator are still alive
+        RenderSystem::shutdown();
 
         mAutoParamsBuffer.reset();
 
